The BBC presenter spotted the pair having a lengthy chat as they observed Trooping the Colour participants march toward Buckingham Palace. The Queen did not personally take the salute on Horse Guards Parade due to ongoing mobility issues but was treated to soldiers performing in her honour on the way back from the ceremony. The Duke of Kent stood ramrod straight next to his eldest cousin, seemingly exchanging commentary about the performance, leaving Huw Edwards "fascinated" and wondering about their conversation.   Mr Edwards said: "I have to say I am fascinated. "This long conversation between the Queen and the Duke of Kent. "They're obviously comparing notes and pointing to this section of the Guard, that section of the Guard. "I'd love to know what they're saying." MORE TO FOLLOW...